        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 2:53PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 253 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cuchillo. This thunderstorm was drifting southeast at about 5 mph,
and will cross Interstate 10 shortly.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cuchillo, Truth or Consequences, City of Elephant Butte, Alamosa
Canyon, Williamsburg, Elephant Butte Lake, Lost Canyon, Ash Canyon,
Rock Canyon, Hot Springs Landing, Lakeshore Highlands, South
Monticello Campground, and Lions Beach.

This includes Interstate 25 in New Mexico between mile markers 73 and
88.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
